  "nursesNote": "Autism spectrum disorder is a developmental condition with deficits in social communication and interaction along with restricted, repetitive behaviors; it varies widely (a spectrum). A child may have delayed or atypical speech, poor eye contact, repetitive behaviors (stimming), fixed interests, a strong preference for routine and sameness, and sensory sensitivities. The nurse keeps routines consistent, prepares the child before any change, and uses simple, concrete, literal communication with visual aids. Reducing sensory overload (noise, lights) helps, and a familiar comfort item eases anxiety. The nurse ensures safety (wandering, self-injury), individualizes care, and works closely with caregivers who know the child best.",
  "providerOrders": [
    "Keep routines consistent and prepare for changes",
    "Use simple, concrete communication and visual aids",
    "Reduce sensory overload (noise and bright lights)",
    "Ensure safety from wandering and self-injury",
    "Involve caregivers and individualize care"
  ],
